,"dimensions":55},"Large, quite finely cut Greek letters: Alpha with straight bar, Epsilon with shorter middle bar, theta and omicron full size, xsi of the form of a Z with split and curled diagonal, standard four-bar sigma, omega of classical form, partly open.",[56,61],{"type":57,"l":58,"from":59,"to":59,"unit":60},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","mm",{"type":62,"l":63,"from":59,"to":64,"unit":60},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2",{"_":66,"notBefore":67,"notAfter":68},"Possibly Hellenistic in date?",-250,-1,[70,75],{"_":71,"type":72,"ref":73,"region":74},"Syracusae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462503","Sicilia",{"_":76,"type":77,"ref":78,"region":74},"Siracusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2523083",[80],[81,82],37.08415,15.27628,{"_":84,"type":85,"subtype":86,"geo":17},"First seen and described by Ottavio Gaetani (1566-1620), who observed it in the chapel of Castello Maniace (Ortygia), but who recorded that it had previously been transported there by the spanish commander, from the church of St. John (i.e. the catacombs of S. Giovanni); it was then moved to the Duomo in 1644 and after the earthquake of 1693 replaced the old baptismal font.","found","discovered",[],{"_":89,"type":90,"subtype":91,"geo":17},"None","observed","autopsied",[],"Sicily",{"_":95,"role":96},"Duomo di Siracusa","other",{"_":98,"mainLang":99,"languages":100},"Ancient Greek","grc",[98],{"type":102,"bibl":103},"edition",[104,113,121,132,141,152,165],{"author":105,"date":106,"citedRange":107,"ptr":108,"ref":109,"inscriptionDate":106,"title":110,"citation":111,"uri":112,"year":106},"Gualtherus","1624","204",{"target":109},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GIN6NANU","Siciliae obiacentium insular et Bruttiorum antiquae tabulae cum animadversionibus Georgii Gualtheri","\u003Cspan>G. Gualtherus, \u003Ci>Siciliae obiacentium insular et Bruttiorum antiquae tabulae cum animadversionibus Georgii Gualtheri\u003C/i> (Panormi, 1624)\u003C/span>","https://www.zo