Date":167,"title":173,"citation":174,"uri":175,"year":167},"Ferrua","1940","74-81",{"target":170},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/UC29MPZC",{"_":172,"target":172},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002002","Nuovi studi nelle catacombe di Siracusa","\u003Cspan>Antonio Ferrua, «Nuovi studi nelle catacombe di Siracusa», \u003Ci>Rivista di Archeologia Cristiana\u003C/i> 17 (1940): 43–81\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/UC29MPZC",{"type":177,"bibl":178},"discussion",[17],{"editor":180,"principal":183,"contributors":184,"change":188},{"_":181,"ref":182},"Jonathan Prag","#JP",{"_":181,"ref":182},[185],{"_":181,"xml:id":186,"ref":187},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":189,"when":190,"who":182},"Jonathan Prag created draft file","2026-03-02","",[],[194,195,196,197,198,199,200],"Gualtherus, 1624, Siciliae obiacentium insular et Bruttiorum antiquae tabulae cum animadversionibus Georgii Gualtheri","Gualtherus, 1624 [1625], Siciliæ obiacentium insular. et Bruttiorum antiquæ tabulæ, cum animadversionib","Castelli, 1769, Siciliae et objacentium insularum veterum inscriptionum nova collectio","Castelli, 1784, Siciliae et objacentium insularum veterum inscriptionum nova collectio prolegomenis et notis illustrata, et iterum cum emendationibus, & auctariis evulgata","Capodieci, 1813, Antichi monumenti di Siracusa","Curtius, Kirchhoff, Roehl, 1877, CIG","Ferrua, 1940, Nuovi studi nelle catacombe di Siracusa",[202,203,204,205,206,207,208],"GIN6NANU","ZP8DE8KS","SPTB56H3","7PSFHSUH","4A4U5FEA","533T8HNS","UC29MPZC",[210,211,212,19,24,28,213,214,215,216,214,217,218,99],"isic002128","dedication of a marble basin",{"_":5},"syracusae","siracusa","sicilia","sicily","duomo di siracusa","ancient greek",[],{"title":221,"body":222,"divs":223,"editions":248,"images":258,"handnote":259},"ISic002128. Dedication of a marble basin","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΝΑΘΗ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]Ι ΙΙΙ\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">. 20.\u003C/span>]ΣΜΑ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΞΙΜΟΥΘΕΟΔΩΡΟΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">. 14.\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">..\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΤΟΝΚΡΑΤΗΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">. 14.\u003C/span>]ΡΟΝ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΝΑΘΗ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΙΙΙΙ\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">····················\u003C/span>]ΣΜΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΞΙΜΟΥΘΕΟΔΩΡΟΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··············\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΤΟΝΚΡΑΤΗΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··············\u003C/span>]ΡΟΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text of Ferrua\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This is a preliminary record, reporting the reading of Ferrua, and some of the primary bibliography. Fresh autopsy is required. The inscription has an unfortunate history, recounted fully by Ferrua, such that it was rapidly transformed into a text associated with a later Christian tradition and supposely recording its dedication as a font for baptism (through the insertion by Gualtherus/Mirabella, of the word βαπτισματος into line 1). Consequently, although included in CIG by Kirchhoff, it was completely omitted by Kaibel (on the view that it was 8th century or later), and has been almost entirely ignored since. As Ferrua notes, on this occasion Torremuzza was a much more reliable witness than Gualtherus. The text clearly contains reference to a dedication (ἀνάθημα) and to the object itself, τὸν κρατῆρα. Line 2 appears to contain the name of the dedicant. Line 1 likely contained the name of the divinity to whom the object was dedicated\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 204 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 98 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 cl.17 no.1 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 cl.17 no.1 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Capodieci 1813 vol. 1, §25, pp. 121-126 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002092\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002092\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kirchhoff 1877 8886 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1940 74-81 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002002\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002002\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Large, quite finely cut Greek letters: Alpha with straight bar, Epsilon with shorter middle bar, theta and omicron full size, xsi of the form of a Z with split and curled diagonal, standard four-bar sigma, omega of classical form, partly open.\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[224,227,230,233,236,239,242,245],{"id":225,"html":226},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΝΑΘΗ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]Ι ΙΙΙ\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">. 20.\u003C/span>]ΣΜΑ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΞΙΜΟΥΘΕΟΔΩΡΟΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">. 14.\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">..\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΤΟΝΚΡΑΤΗΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">. 14.\u003C/span>]ΡΟΝ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΝΑΘΗ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΙΙΙΙ\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">····················\u003C/span>]ΣΜΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΞΙΜΟΥΘΕΟΔΩΡΟΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··············\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΤΟΝΚΡΑΤΗΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··············\u003C/span>]ΡΟΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":228,"html":229},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>",{"id":231,"html":232},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text of Ferrua\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":234,"html":235},"translation","\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":237,"html":238},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This is a preliminary record, reporting the reading of Ferrua, and some of the primary bibliography. Fresh autopsy is required. The inscription has an unfortunate history, recounted fully by Ferrua, such that it was rapidly transformed into a text associated with a later Christian tradition and supposely recording its dedication as a font for baptism (through the insertion by Gualtherus/Mirabella, of the word βαπτισματος into line 1). Consequently, although included in CIG by Kirchhoff, it was completely omitted by Kaibel (on the view that it was 8th century or later), and has been almost entirely ignored since. As Ferrua notes, on this occasion Torremuzza was a much more reliable witness than Gualtherus. The text clearly contains reference to a dedication (ἀνάθημα) and to the object itself, τὸν κρατῆρα. Line 2 appears to contain the name of the dedicant. Line 1 likely contained the name of the divinity to whom the object was dedicated\u003C/p>  ",{"id":240,"html":241},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 204 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 98 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 cl.17 no.1 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 cl.17 no.1 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Capodieci 1813 vol. 1, §25, pp. 121-126 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002092\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002092\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kirchhoff 1877 8886 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrua 1940 74-81 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002002\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002002\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":243,"html":244},"handnote","\u003Cp>Large, quite finely cut Greek letters: Alpha with straight bar, Epsilon with shorter middle bar, theta and omicron full size, xsi of the form of a Z with split and curled diagonal, standard four-bar sigma, omega of classical form, partly open.\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":246,"html":247},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[249,251,254,255],{"html":250},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":252,"lang":99,"html":253},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΝΑΘΗ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]Ι ΙΙΙ\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">.\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">. 20.\u003C/span>]ΣΜΑ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΞΙΜΟΥΘΕΟΔΩΡΟΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">. 14.\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">..\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΤΟΝΚΡΑΤΗΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">. 14.\u003C/span>]ΡΟΝ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":250},{"id":256,"lang":99,"html":257},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΑΝΑΘΗ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΙΙΙΙ\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">·\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">····················\u003C/span>]ΣΜΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΞΙΜΟΥΘΕΟΔΩΡΟΣ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··············\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΤΟΝΚΡΑΤΗΡΑ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">··············\u003C/span>]ΡΟΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[],[260],{"html":54},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Dedication of a marble basin\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic002128\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002128\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Siracusa\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"other\">Duomo di Siracusa\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003C!--No inventory number found-->\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>A large stone krater, or vase, with simple pedestal foot, rim, and two handles. Judged by Ferrua to be a compact local limestone, rather than a marble. The text is heavily worn and not entirely legible\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.limestone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html\">limestone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.basin\" ref=\"https://www.e agle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/144.html\">basin\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--Ferrua-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">77\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">80\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.complete\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Three lines of text, on one side of the basin, with line 1 on the outside of the rim, and lines 2-3 on the belly of the krater below the rim.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.deteriorated\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Large, quite finely cut Greek letters: Alpha with straight bar, Epsilon with shorter middle bar, theta and omicron full size, xsi of the form of a Z with split and curled diagonal, standard four-bar sigma, omega of classical form, partly open.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462503\">Syracusae\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2523083\">Siracusa\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.08415, 15.27628\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0250\" notAfter-custom=\"-0001\">Possibly Hellenistic in date?\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\">First seen and described by Ottavio Gaetani (1566-1620), who observed it in the chapel of Castello Maniace (Ortygia), but who recorded that it had previously been transported there by the spanish commander, from the church of St. John (i.e. the catacombs of S. Giovanni); it was then moved to the Duomo in 1644 and after the earthquake of 1693 replaced the old baptismal font.\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">None\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.dedication\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html\">dedication\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"draft\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n               \u003Cchange when=\"2026-03-02\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag created draft file\u003C/change>\n            \u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\u003Csurface/>\u003C!-- \n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic002128_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic002128.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface> -->\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>ΑΝΑΘΗ\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>Ι ΙΙΙ\u003Cgap reason=\"illegible\" unit=\"character\" quantity=\"1\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" unit=\"character\" quantity=\"20\" precision=\"medium\"/>ΣΜΑ\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>ΞΙΜΟΥΘΕΟΔΩΡΟΣ\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" unit=\"character\" quantity=\"14\" precision=\"medium\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"illegible\" unit=\"character\" quantity=\"2\"/>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>ΤΟΝΚΡΑΤΗΡΑ\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" unit=\"character\" quantity=\"14\" precision=\"medium\"/>ΡΟΝ\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\n                        \u003Cnote>Text of Ferrua\u003C/note>\n                    \u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\">\n                \u003Cp>\u003C!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>This is a preliminary record, reporting the reading of Ferrua, and some of the primary bibliography. Fresh autopsy is required. The inscription has an unfortunate history, recounted fully by Ferrua, such that it was rapidly transformed into a text associated with a later Christian tradition and supposely recording its dedication as a font for baptism (through the insertion by Gualtherus/Mirabella, of the word βαπτισματος into line 1). Consequently, although included in CIG by Kirchhoff, it was completely omitted by Kaibel (on the view that it was 8th century or later), and has been almost entirely ignored since. As Ferrua notes, on this occasion Torremuzza was a much more reliable witness than Gualtherus. The text clearly contains reference to a dedication (ἀνάθημα) and to the object itself, τὸν κρατῆρα. Line 2 appears to contain the name of the dedicant. Line 1 likely contained the name of the divinity to whom the object was dedicated\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Gualtherus\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1624\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>204\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GIN6NANU\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Gualtherus\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1624 [1625]\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>98\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/ZP8DE8KS\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Castelli\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1769\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>cl.17 no.1\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/SPTB56H3\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Castelli\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1784\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>cl.17 no.1\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/7PSFHSUH\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Capodieci\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1813\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>vol. 1, §25, pp. 121-126\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4A4U5FEA\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002092\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002092\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"CIG\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Kirchhoff\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1877\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>8886\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/533T8HNS\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001249\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Ferrua\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1940\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>74-81\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/UC29MPZC\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002002\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002002\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
